Method Detail

binaryToGray

public static int binaryToGray(int num)
The purpose of this function is to convert an unsigned binary number to reflected binary Gray code. For example the integer value 2 is represented in binary code as: 0000.....0010 2 is represented in gray code as: 0000.....0011 (3 in binary) binarytoGray( 2 ) = 3

Parameters:
num - Integer number to be converted to Gray code
Returns:
Integer value that represents the value num (in binary format)

Returns:
Number of bits required for representing such n different values

grayToBinary

public static int grayToBinary(int num)
The purpose of this function is to convert a reflected binary Gray code number to a binary number. For example, 0000.....0011 in binary code represents 3, but in Gray code represents 2. grayToBinary( 3 ) = 2

Parameters:
num - Integer number in Gray code that will be converted to Binary code
Returns:
Integer value that is represented by the value num (using Gray code)
